title: $:/plugins/nikorion/hover-tilt/language/en-GB/readme
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

!! Overview

A `<$HoverTilt>` widget bringing [[hover-tilt|https://hover-tilt.simey.me]]'s 3D tilt/glare pointer effect to any TiddlyWiki content — the same effect used on the [[Pokémon holo cards demo|https://hover-tilt.simey.me/bespoke/pokemon-cards/]].

hover-tilt ships its own prebuilt Web Component — a self-registering, dependency-free `<hover-tilt>` custom element. `modules/hover-tilt.min.js` vendors that file as-is (TiddlyWiki module header added, its one ESM `export` statement removed), and the `<$HoverTilt>` widget loads it via `require()` like any other TiddlyWiki module, then drives the resulting `<hover-tilt>` element directly.

* `<$HoverTilt>` — wraps whatever content is written in its own body with hover-tilt's 3D tilt/glare effect

---

!! Body / slotted content

hover-tilt applies its tilt effect to whatever is written in its own body — not to a fixed element (see its [[bespoke docs|https://hover-tilt.simey.me/bespoke/pokemon-cards/]] for a real-world example). `<$HoverTilt>` mirrors that: anything nested inside the widget's own tags is rendered by TiddlyWiki as usual, then becomes hover-tilt's slotted content.

<$codeblock code="""<$HoverTilt><img src="card.png" style="width:220px;border-radius:12px;"/></$HoverTilt>"""/>

Used self-closing / with no body, the widget just tilts nothing (an empty slot).

---

!! Attributes

Every attribute below is a direct pass-through to [[hover-tilt|https://hover-tilt.simey.me]] — see its docs for the full behaviour of each.

Each value is resolved in three tiers: the widget attribute, then the global setting tiddler `$:/plugins/nikorion/hover-tilt/settings/<attr>` (edited via the //Hover Tilt// tab in [[Control Panel|$:/ControlPanel]]), then hover-tilt's own internal default. The //Default// column below is the plugin's shipped setting; leave an attribute out to inherit it.

|!Attribute |!Values |!Default |!Description |
| `tiltFactor` |number |`1.2` |Tilt intensity multiplier |
| `tiltFactorY` |number |same as `tiltFactor` |Separate Y-axis tilt factor |
| `scaleFactor` |number |`1` |Scale-up amount while active |
| `stiffness` |number |`0.066` |Spring stiffness (scale/opacity) — higher is snappier. Default matches the Pokémon holo cards' soft interaction spring, not hover-tilt's own (snappier) `0.2` |
| `damping` |number |`0.25` |Spring damping (scale/opacity) — higher is less bouncy. Default matches the Pokémon holo cards, not hover-tilt's own `0.8` |
| `tiltStiffness` |number |= `stiffness` |Stiffness of a //separate// tilt spring — omit to reuse the scale spring |
| `tiltDamping` |number |= `damping` |Damping of the separate tilt spring — omit to reuse the scale spring |
| `enterDelay` |number (ms) |`0` |Delay before activating on pointer enter |
| `exitDelay` |number (ms) |`200` |Delay before deactivating on pointer leave |
| `shadow` |`yes` · `no` |`yes` |Drop shadow that follows the tilt |
| `shadowBlur` |number |`12` |Shadow blur radius |
| `blendMode` |CSS blend mode |`overlay` |`mix-blend-mode` for the glare layer |
| `glareIntensity` |number |`1` |Glare opacity multiplier |
| `glareHue` |number (0-360) |`270` |Glare colour hue |
| `glareMask` |CSS `mask-image` value |— |Masks the glare layer to a shape |
| `glareMaskMode` |CSS `mask-mode` value |hover-tilt's own |`match-source` · `luminance` · `alpha` · `none` |
| `glareMaskComposite` |CSS `mask-composite` value |hover-tilt's own |`add` · `subtract` · `exclude` · `intersect` |
| `borderRadius` |CSS length |`12px` |Baseline corner radius of the host (glare/shadow layers inherit it) |
| `class` |string |— |Extra CSS class(es) on hover-tilt's container |
| `style` |string |— |Extra inline style on hover-tilt's container, appended after the widget's required `display: inline-block; border-radius: <borderRadius>;` baseline |

!!! Corner radius: a single source of truth

hover-tilt's glare/shadow layers live in its //shadow DOM// and inherit their `border-radius` from the **host** (the `<hover-tilt>` element), not from your content. Rounding only your card therefore leaves the glare/shadow with square corners (or the `12px` default).

To set the radius **once**, put the real value on the widget's `borderRadius` attribute and `border-radius: inherit` on your content: the content then picks up the host's radius, and glare + shadow + content stay aligned. Hard-coding the radius on both sides instead forces you to keep them in sync by hand.

---

